[center][size=6]NPC Memory[/size]

[i]NPCs remember your daily activities and comment on them based on their personal interests. Fish a lot? Willy will notice. Explore the mines? Abigail wants to hear about it![/i][/center]

[line]

[size=5]How It Works[/size]

The mod tracks what you do each day — fishing, mining, farming, cooking, combat, and more. The next morning, NPCs who share an interest in those activities may comment on what you did. Each NPC has unique dialogue lines that match their personality.

[b]Example:[/b] You spend a day fishing and catch 8 fish including a Catfish. The next morning:
[list]
[*][b]Willy[/b]: "Ye caught Catfish yesterday? Fine work! That's a 8-catch day — not bad at all, matey."
[*][b]Elliott[/b]: "I noticed you were fishing yesterday... Catfish — what a magnificent catch! The ocean provides endlessly."
[*][b]Linus[/b]: "Fishing... there's nothing more peaceful. Did you catch Catfish? That's a fine one."
[/list]

Not every NPC will comment every day — there's a configurable chance (default 30%) to keep things feeling natural.

[line]

[size=5]Tracked Activities[/size]

[code]
Activity        | How It's Tracked
----------------+--------------------------------------------------
Fishing         | Catching fish (any type)
Mining          | Collecting gems, minerals, ores, visiting mines
Farming         | Harvesting vegetables and fruits
Cooking         | Preparing cooked dishes
Combat          | Defeating monsters (monster loot drops)
Foraging        | Collecting wild items
Animal Care     | Collecting eggs, milk, animal products
Artisan Goods   | Producing artisan items (wine, cheese, etc.)
Flowers         | Picking flowers
Beverages       | Making beer, wine, coffee, tea, mead, etc.
Sweets          | Baking cakes, cookies, puddings, etc.
Technology      | Collecting bars, battery packs, gadgets
Void Items      | Finding void eggs, void essence, void mayo
Magic           | Handling solar/void essence, arcane materials
[/code]

[line]

