[line]

[size=5]Dialogue System[/size]

[list]
[*]Each NPC has [b]unique, personality-driven dialogue[/b] for their interests
[*]Dialogues reference [b]specific items[/b] you collected and [b]quantities[/b]
[*]If no NPC-specific dialogue exists, a generic fallback is used
[*]NPCs pick the activity you did [b]most[/b] among their interests
[*]Memory stores the [b]last 7 days[/b] of activity history per save
[/list]

[line]

[size=5]Configuration[/size]

All options can be changed via [b]Generic Mod Config Menu[/b] or by editing [font=Courier New]config.json[/font]:

[code]
Option              | Default | Description
--------------------+---------+---------------------------------------------------
EnableMod           | true    | Enable or disable the mod
DialogueChance      | 0.3     | Chance (0.1 - 1.0) each interested NPC will comment
ShowDebugMessages   | false   | Log activity tracking and dialogue injection to console
[/code]

[line]

[size=5]Installation[/size]

[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://smapi.io/]SMAPI[/url] (4.0+)
[*][i](Optional)[/i] Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/5098]Generic Mod Config Menu[/url] for in-game configuration
[*]Download this mod and unzip it into your [font=Courier New]Stardew Valley/Mods[/font] folder
[*]Launch the game through SMAPI
[/list]

[line]

[size=5]Compatibility[/size]

[list]
[*]Stardew Valley [b]1.6+[/b]
[*]Windows, macOS, and Linux
[*]Single-player and multiplayer
[*]Compatible with most other mods (no Harmony patches used)
[/list]

[line]

[size=5]Supported Languages[/size]

[list]
[*]English (default)
[*]Portugues (Brazilian)
[/list]

Want to help translate? Create a new file in the [font=Courier New]i18n[/font] folder following the [url=https://stardewvalleywiki.com/Modding:Translations]SMAPI translation guide[/url].

